Steve Case’s Investment Firm Raises $450 Million for Growth Fund

-- B y   S a b r i n a   W i l l m e r
-- 
2011-12-01T15:00:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-01/steve-case-s-investment-firm-raises-450-million-for-growth-fund.html
Revolution LLC, an investment firm
started by America Online Inc. co-founder  Steve Case , raised
$450 million for the Revolution Growth fund.  The amount exceeds the fund’s $400 million target,
Washington-based Revolution said today in a statement.  Revolution Growth plans to make 10 to 12 investments over a
five-year period, focusing on high-growth companies in the
Eastern U.S. with “the potential to disrupt existing business
models,” according to the statement. The fund’s first
investment is will be made early next year.  In addition to case, Revolution Growth is run by former AOL
senior executives  Ted Leonsis  and Donn Davis.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sabrina Willmer in New York at 
 swillmer2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
